The paper discusses the development of an algorithm portfolio framework for optimization problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of selection strategies, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms, falling under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance measurement of optimization algorithms, which is a topic related to statistical learning, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the use of portfolios, which is a topic related to decision making, falling under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
